      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the high-revving 3.6L M96 flat-six, outputting 320 hp through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row retrofit, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) remains dry. The chassis retains its communicative MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear geometry, benefiting from recent bushing refreshes. While the finish shows minor road-going patina, the engine's power band is linear, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the signature feedback enthusiasts crave. Recent preventive maintenance includes a new Air-Oil Separator (AOS) and a low-temp thermostat, ensuring thermal stability during spirited driving.",
